ENTRY       EC 2.1.1.295                Enzyme
NAME        2-methyl-6-phytyl-1,4-hydroquinone methyltransferase;
            VTE3 (gene name);
            2-methyl-6-solanyl-1,4-hydroquinone methyltransferase;
            MPBQ/MSBQ methyltransferase;
            MPBQ/MSBQ MT
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring one-carbon groups;
            Methyltransferases
SYSNAME     S-adenosyl-L-methionine:2-methyl-6-phytyl-1,4-benzoquinol C3-methyltransferase
REACTION    (1) S-adenosyl-L-methionine + 2-methyl-6-phytylbenzene-1,4-diol = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + 2,3-dimethyl-6-phytylbenzene-1,4-diol [RN:R07501];
            (2) S-adenosyl-L-methionine + 2-methyl-6-all-trans-nonaprenylbenzene-1,4-diol = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + plastoquinol [RN:R10709];
            (3) S-adenosyl-L-methionine + 6-geranylgeranyl-2-methylbenzene-1,4-diol = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + 6-geranylgeranyl-2,3-dimethylbenzene-1,4-diol [RN:R10710]
ALL_REAC    R07501 R10709 R10710
SUBSTRATE   S-adenosyl-L-methionine [CPD:C00019];
            2-methyl-6-phytylbenzene-1,4-diol [CPD:C15882];
            2-methyl-6-all-trans-nonaprenylbenzene-1,4-diol [CPD:C17570];
            6-geranylgeranyl-2-methylbenzene-1,4-diol [CPD:C20737]
PRODUCT     S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine [CPD:C00021];
            2,3-dimethyl-6-phytylbenzene-1,4-diol [CPD:C15883];
            plastoquinol [CPD:C16693];
            6-geranylgeranyl-2,3-dimethylbenzene-1,4-diol [CPD:C20738]
COMMENT     Involved in the biosynthesis of plastoquinol, as well as vitamin E (tocopherols and tocotrienols).
